The teachable concept here is the PPL `date` matcher (time-limited grants), which is implemented only in the Pomerium Zero / Enterprise policy engine, not in open-source Core. The sealed harness runs Core from a config file, which rejects `date` at startup with "unknown policy criterion: date", so the time-window enforcement can't be sealed here. Verified manually against Pomerium Zero (allowed before a future date; 403 after) and the jit-example app's API-driven grants. A generic authenticated_user allow/deny would run in Core but wouldn't demonstrate the date mechanism, so it's intentionally not used.
